Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00glj6g
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 18 May 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Othman Belbeisi, from the International Organization for Migration, describes trying to rescue migrants from Misrata as the Libyan port came under fire. Marcia Clark, the lead prosecutor in the OJ Simpson trial explains why the case changed her life and Cameroonian activist Henriette Ekwe on the price she's paid for a life of political struggle. Show less